## Introduction {#introduction}

This guide explains how to connect Jenkins to GitHub and automatically trigger jobs when code is pushed to your repository.

### What You'll Learn
- How to set up GitHub webhook
- How to add GitHub credentials to Jenkins
- How to create a Jenkins pipeline job
- How to create a Jenkinsfile
- How to troubleshoot common issues

---

## Prerequisites {#prerequisites}

### What You Need
- Jenkins server (running and accessible)
- GitHub account with a repository
- Admin access to Jenkins
- Admin access to GitHub repo
- Internet connection between Jenkins and GitHub

### Required Jenkins Plugins

```
Jenkins → Manage Jenkins → Manage Plugins
→ Available → Search "GitHub"
→ Install "GitHub Integration Plugin"
→ Restart Jenkins
```

