### STEP 5: Create Jenkinsfile in Your Repo

#### 5.1 Create Jenkinsfile

```
Create file in repo root: Jenkinsfile
```

#### 5.2 Add Pipeline Code

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any
    
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                checkout scm
                echo "Code checked out successfully!"
            }
        }
        
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                echo "Building application..."
                sh 'echo "Build step"'
            }
        }
        
        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                echo "Running tests..."
                sh 'echo "Test step"'
            }
        }
        
        stage('Deploy') {
            steps {
                echo "Deploying..."
                sh 'echo "Deploy step"'
            }
        }
    }
    
    post {
        success {
            echo '✅ Build Success!'
        }
        failure {
            echo '❌ Build Failed!'
        }
    }
}
```

#### 5.3 Push Jenkinsfile to GitHub

```bash
git add Jenkinsfile
git commit -m "Add Jenkinsfile for Jenkins CI/CD"
git push origin main
```

