## How It Works {#how-it-works}

### Automatic Flow (With Webhook)

```
1. Developer pushes code to GitHub
   git push origin main

2. GitHub detects the push
   Checks for active webhooks

3. GitHub sends webhook request
   POST /github-webhook/
   With: commit SHA, branch, author, etc.

4. Jenkins receives webhook
   Triggers the job

5. Jenkins uses credentials
   Authenticates to GitHub
   Clones the repository

6. Jenkins reads Jenkinsfile
   Parses pipeline stages

7. Jenkins executes pipeline
   - Checkout
   - Build
   - Test
   - Deploy

8. Build completes
   Success or failure status sent to GitHub

9. GitHub shows build status on commit
   Green checkmark or red X
```

### Manual Flow (Without Webhook)

```
1. Developer pushes code to GitHub
   git push origin main

2. Developer goes to Jenkins
   Jenkins → my-app-ci job

3. Developer clicks "Build Now"
   Manual trigger

4. Jenkins uses credentials
   Authenticates to GitHub
   Clones the repository

5. Jenkins reads Jenkinsfile
   Parses pipeline stages

6. Jenkins executes pipeline
   Same as automatic

7. Build completes
   Success or failure
```

