## Common Mistakes {#common-mistakes}

```
❌ WRONG: http://jenkins.company.com:8080/my-app/github-webhook/
✓ RIGHT: http://jenkins.company.com:8080/github-webhook/

❌ WRONG: Forgot to check "GitHub hook trigger" in job
✓ RIGHT: Check the box and save

❌ WRONG: Jenkins URL is localhost or private IP
✓ RIGHT: Use public IP or domain name

❌ WRONG: Jenkinsfile in subfolder
✓ RIGHT: Jenkinsfile in repo root

❌ WRONG: Credentials not selected in job
✓ RIGHT: Select "github-credentials" from dropdown

❌ WRONG: Token expired
✓ RIGHT: Check token expiration date

❌ WRONG: Repository URL doesn't match
✓ RIGHT: Use exact same URL in Jenkins job

❌ WRONG: Firewall blocks port 8080
✓ RIGHT: Allow port 8080 through firewall
```

